11) deleting files : https://www.tecmint.com/delete-all-files-in-directory-except-one-few-file-extensions/

12) rm -r !(pdfs)

13) recover deleted things :  https://www.kalilinux.in/2019/09/foremost-kali-linux-recover-deleted-files.html


14) deleting multiple files : https://linuxize.com/post/how-to-remove-files-and-directories-using-linux-command-line/    ==>> rm -r dir1 dir2 dir3 


15) SIZE OF FOLDER  ::    du -sh folder_or_file

16) regex :  rm -r *der  /// remove all folder ending with der
             rm *ile     /// remove all file ending eith ile
             rm -r fol*  /// remove all folder satrting with fol
             rm -r *old*  // removbe all folder whose name consists 'old'
             same applied with mv , cp, cd|
